---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, '/');
---

<Base title="A Mental Model">
  <section class="hero container">
    <p class="hero__subtitle">A framework for the uncertain</p>
    <h1>What should you be doing<br />with your life?</h1>
    <p class="hero__intro">
      Nobody knows. Not really. But there's one answer that survives the uncertainty
      &mdash; and it might change how you think about everything.
    </p>
    <a href={`${base}essay`} class="hero__cta">Read the Essay</a>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="container" style="padding: 2rem 0 4rem; text-align: center;">
    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">The idea in brief</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">
      We don't know the purpose of life. We might never know. But if there <em>is</em>
      a right thing to be doing, the only rational response is to search for it.
    </p>
    <p class="thesis" style="max-width: 540px; margin: 1.5rem auto; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-accent-dark); line-height: 1.5;">
      The purpose of life is to discover the purpose of life.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); max-width: 540px; margin: 1rem auto 0; font-size: 1.05rem;">
      It sounds circular. It isn't. The essay explains why &mdash; and what it means
      for how we live, work, and decide what matters.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="cta-section">
      <h2>This idea gets stronger with pushback</h2>
      <p>
        If this resonates with you &mdash; or if you think it's wrong and can say why
        &mdash; I want to hear from you. The search is better together.
      </p>
      <a href={`${base}essay`} class="hero__cta">Start Reading</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
